Barn: Nils Ture f. 39, Claes 43. — Stud:ex. i Vänersb, 29, med. kand. i Upps. 37, med. Hc. 44. Kort. as’sis’t:- o. und :làk :förordn. v. las. i Vänersb. o. v. Sahlgr. sjukh. i Gbg 44, vik. und :l:äk. v. pens :’Styr. kuranst. i Vänersb. 45, ord. andre und :läk. där 45-47, und :läk:förordn. v. las. i Vänersb. 47. Medl. av Frimurarorden.
translated: Englund, Nils Claes, certified physician, from Vänersborg, born on January 11th, 1909 in Vänersborg to the first provincial physician, medical doctor honoris causa Nils E. and Augusta Mörner. Married in 1938 to Edith Turesson, had two children: Nils Ture born in 1939 and Claes in 1943. Completed high school in Vänersborg in 1929, received a Bachelor of Medicine from Uppsala University in 1937, and a Doctor of Medicine degree in 1944. Held short assistant and deputy physician positions at the hospital in Vänersborg and Sahlgr. Hospital in Gothenburg in 1944, acting deputy physician at the Board of Directors sanatorium in Vänersborg in 1945, regular acting deputy physician there from 1945-1947, and appointed deputy physician at the hospital in Vänersborg in 1947. Member of the Freemason Order.
